# QuickFlow Trivy Ignore File
# Use this file to suppress specific vulnerabilities or false positives
# Always add a comment explaining WHY each item is ignored

# ============================================================================
# FORMAT EXAMPLES:
# ============================================================================
# Ignore specific CVE:           CVE-2024-12345
# Ignore CVE in package:          CVE-2024-12345 pkg:npm/package-name
# Ignore by file path:            CVE-2024-12345 frontend/src/file.ts
# Ignore entire package:          pkg:npm/package-name
# Ignore secrets in file:         secret:rule-name path/to/file
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# DEPENDENCY VULNERABILITIES
# ============================================================================

# Example: Spring Boot 3.3.0 - Known false positive, fixed in 3.3.1
# CVE-2024-XXXXX pkg:maven/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-starter-web

# Example: React 18 - Low severity issue with no exploit available
# CVE-2024-XXXXX pkg:npm/react

# Example: Development dependency - Only used in tests
# CVE-2024-XXXXX pkg:npm/jest

# ============================================================================
# CONFIGURATION MISCONFIGURATIONS
# ============================================================================

# Example: MongoDB connection - Using environment variables in production
# config:mongodb backend/src/main/resources/application.properties

# Example: CORS configuration - Intentionally permissive for localhost development
# config:cors backend/src/main/java/com/ai/application/config/WebConfig.java

# ============================================================================
# SECRET SCANNING FALSE POSITIVES
# ============================================================================

# Example: Documentation containing example API keys
# secret:generic-api-key README.md
# secret:generic-api-key SETUP.md

# Example: Test files with mock JWT tokens
# secret:jwt-token-full backend/src/test/

# Example: Configuration templates with placeholders
# secret:supabase-anon-key frontend/.env.example

# ============================================================================
# LICENSE COMPLIANCE
# ============================================================================

# Example: Acceptable license for specific use case
# license:GPL-3.0 pkg:npm/some-gpl-package

# ============================================================================
# ACCEPTED RISKS
# ============================================================================

# Example: Risk accepted by security team - scheduled fix in Q2 2026
# CVE-2024-XXXXX
# Reason: No known exploit exists, awaiting upstream patch
# Accepted by: Security Team
# Review date: 2026-04-01

# ============================================================================
# YOUR IGNORES BELOW THIS LINE
# ============================================================================

# Add your project-specific ignores here with clear documentation
# Format: CVE/rule identifier followed by explanation comment
